class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="proficiency-design-build" class="entry-website-title">Proficiency Design &amp; Build</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-proficiency-design-build-3840x16242-20240611.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-proficiency-design-build-3840x16242-20240611.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-proficiency-design-build-3840x16242-20240611.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Proficiency Design &amp; Build"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.proficiencyltd.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.proficiencyltd.co.uk/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>London, England, U.K.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Proficiency Design &amp; Build is a well-established company with expertise in residential design, construction, and renovation solutions. The website's clean and efficient design elements contribute to a stylish and professional visual appeal, complemented by fresh color accents and legible typography.</p><p>The home page's hero image of a sophisticated residential interior, along with its specialist services section, speaks to the company's aesthetic and effectively captures its commitment to quality-first craftsmanship.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>According to WAVE, the website has no contrast errors, indicating optimal readability. Important information, such as the company's working hours, contact options, and industry affiliations, are clearly visible on the website.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website's portfolio page would benefit from additional before-and-after photos for a more informative user experience. WAVE also picked up several errors on the site, including missing form labels.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-proficiency-design-build-3840x16242-20240611.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-proficiency-design-build-3840x16242-20240611.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop website has an aesthetically pleasing appearance with prominent CTA buttons, well-spaced page layouts, and attractive images that convey ideas of quality. A standout feature is the 3D walkthrough video of the company's latest project, but it is hidden on the "About Us" page and should be advertised on the home page for prominence.</p><p>The desktop site's performance scored 100/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights test, indicating faster-than-average page loading times and optimal site navigation with a sticky top menu bar and comprehensive footer menu.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-proficiency-design-and-build-824x16382-20240613.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-proficiency-design-and-build-824x16382-20240613.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site slims the content and images down nicely, remaining high-quality and easy to navigate. As with the desktop version, the 3D walkthrough video is accessible but should also be available on the home page. The sticky hamburger menu is a helpful feature, but the "Request a Quote" CTA button is no longer visible on the site. The website's performance remains well-scored at 92/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights test.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="synder-construction-group" class="entry-website-title">Synder Construction Group</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-snyder-construction-group-3840x13403-20240611.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-snyder-construction-group-3840x13403-20240611.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-snyder-construction-group-3840x13403-20240611.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Synder Construction Group"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.snydercg.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.snydercg.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Ozark, Missouri, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Synder Construction Group is an industry-leading commercial construction company with a strong local presence. The website's home page has a dynamic appearance with a transitional hero image and geometric motif that enhances its professional aesthetic. The site's easy navigation and content-rich pages allow visitors to explore the company's past projects and find out more about their building philosophy.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website features a news and videos section that keeps clients informed of the company's latest projects and news, ensuring increased reader engagement. The "Projects" page acts as a showcase of the company's work with impactful images, reflecting their ethos of reliable workmanship. On WAVE, the site has only a few contrast errors.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The company's social media links at the bottom of the home page are quite small and easy to miss, while the lack of a dedicated client testimonials section hinders company credibility. The site's lengthy paragraphs could be broken up with additional images or interactive elements so as to not overwhelm readers.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-snyder-construction-group-3840x13403-20240611.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-snyder-construction-group-3840x13403-20240611.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop website functions well with straightforward navigation and polished design elements, reflected in its performance score of 98/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights test. All pertinent information is readily available on the website, but visitors can use the online contact form to easily get in touch with the company. In terms of readability, the footer menu's text could be sized up slightly to match the prominent contact info.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-snyder-construction-group-824x14900-20240611.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-snyder-construction-group-824x14900-20240611.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>On the mobile site, a gridline visibly runs through the text, which takes away from the aesthetically pleasing website design. The interactive images and text work well on the mobile site, but the top menu bar does not float down the page when scrolling, hindering navigation. The site scored 66/100 in the performance category on Google's PageSpeed Insights test, indicating slow page loading times.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
